Paleoenvironment . The Paratethyan occurrences derive from inner neritic, coastal and lagoonal settings (e.g. Korneuburg Basin and North Alpine Foreland Basin, Harzhauser et al . 2002;
Zuschin et al . 2004
). At many localities, it occurs in huge numbers forming “turritelline-dominated assemblages” sensu Allmon & Knight (1993) .

